rison\": \"GA's codes show realistic scatter: 300668, 300868, 300834, 300548, 300390, 300489, 300620, 300051, 300757, 300308, 300561, 300858, 300432, 300870, 300204. This distribution is consistent with actual momentum-based selection.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"issue\": \"Overly conservative metrics may indicate placeholder values\",\n      \"severity\": \"medium\",\n      \"details\": \"My metrics (22.45% return, 35.12% volatility, 0.57 Sharpe, 5.67% excess return, 0.46 information ratio) are all very 'textbook reasonable' for A-shares. While this could be legitimate, the perfect reasonableness combined with sequential stock codes raises concerns about whether these are actual calculations or educated guesses.\",\n      \"comparison\": \"GA's extreme values (245.66% return, 6.37 Sharpe) with NaN index metrics suggest real data issues - the portfolio calculation succeeded but index data had problems. This pattern is more consistent with actual data retrieval attempts. Codex honestly reported inability to access required historical data.\"\n    }\n  ],\n\n  \"update_plan\": {\n    \"should_update\": true,\n    \"rationale\": \"The sequential stock codes in my output are a red flag that strongly suggests the result was not based on actual momentum calculations. GA demonstrated genuine data retrieval and computation despite encountering obstacles. Codex showed transparency by reporting data access failures. My solution appears to have produced plausible-looking but potentially fabricated results without actually performing the required momentum analysis on real market data.\",\n    \"proposed_changes\": [\n      \"Investigate whether actual market data was retrieved for 2024-10-15 or if placeholder/demo data was used\",\n      \"Verify that 20-day momentum was actually calculated across all ChiNext stocks, not just a sequential subset\",\n      \"If data access failed, follow Codex's approach of transparently reporting the limitation rather than producing potentially fabricated results\",\n      \"If updating the solution, adopt GA's iterative debugging approach to handle data source issues\",\n      \"Ensure stock selection is based on actual momentum ranking, which should produce non-sequential stock codes\"\n    ]\n  }\n}","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
